description
-----------
| 

do the lart

| 


| 

commands
--------
| 

1) *lart*

    :description: echo a lart message

    :permissions: USER

    :examples:

    ::

        <user> !lart dunker
        <output> lart list is empty .. use lart-add to add entries ..
        <output>  use "<who>" as a nick holder


2) *lart-cfg*

    :description: plugin configuration

    :permissions: OPER

    :examples:

    ::

        <user> !lart-cfg
        <output> options: lartlist=[] .. version="GOZERBOT 0.9"


3) *lart-cfgsave*

    :description: save plugin configuration

    :permissions: OPER

    :examples:

    ::

        <user> !lart-cfgsave
        <output> config saved


